Alastair Cook feared Jonathan Trott was out of international cricket 18 months ago . 
  The Warwickshire batsman has returned to the international scene and is set to open the batting for England in West Indies . 
  Trott left the 2013/14 Ashes with stress and anxiety . 
  Test captain Cook feels the batsman is ready for the 'pressure cooker' of international life . 
 